\\ Q\\right)\\ \\times\\ \\left(\\frac{1}{V}\\right)\n</annotation>\n</semantics>\n</math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathit mtight\">D</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">\u200b</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">P</span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mbin\">\u00d7</span></span><span class=\"mord mathit\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">Q</span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\">)</span></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mbin\">\u00d7</span></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mspace\">\u00a0</span><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">(</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathit mtight\">V</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\"></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">\u200b</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\ufeff\n", "\nThis means the demand for money is proportional to nominal income and the inverse of the velocity of money. Economists typically interpret the inverse of the velocity of money as the demand to hold cash balances, so this version of the equation of exchange shows that the demand for money in an economy is made up of demand for use in transactions, (P x Q), and <a data-component=\"link\" data-ordinal=\"1\" data-source=\"inlineLink\" data-type=\"internalLink\" href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/l/liquidity.asp\">liquidity</a> demand, (1/V).\n"]}